</string>

<!-- ===== TURN 2: Player asked for details ===== -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_choice_1">
    <text>Military container? That's worth investigating. Send the location.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_choice_2">
    <text>Could be someone's personal stash. Touching it might start problems.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_choice_3">
    <text>Sealed container in mutant territory? Sounds like bait. I'll pass.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_choice_4">
    <text>Tell me more about those mutant tracks. How many, how fresh?</text>
</string>

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_reply_1">
    <text>Coordinates sent. I marked it right near the vehicle graveyard. Kill whatever's guarding it, crack it open, keep what's inside. Good hunting, $player_name.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_reply_2">
    <text>This deep in the Zone, "personal property" doesn't exist anymore. Everything belongs to whoever can hold it. But sure, your conscience, your call.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_reply_3">
    <text>Paranoid, but I get it. Plenty of stalkers disappeared chasing "sure things." Your caution might keep you alive longer than most.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_1_t2_reply_4">
    <text>Four, maybe five sets of prints. Pseudodog-sized at least. Tracks were maybe a few hours old, hard to tell in the dark. They're circling the area, probably territorial. Not a casual stroll for sure.</text>
</string>

