<!-- SCENARIO: Bandit Ambush Warning in Dark Valley              -->
<!-- A veteran NPC warns the player about a bandit ambush being  -->
<!-- set up near Dark Valley. Player can set a counter-ambush,   -->
<!-- avoid the area, try to negotiate with the bandits through   -->
<!-- the NPC, or use the info to lure the bandits into a mutant  -->
<!-- hotspot. Uses spawn_hostile, location markers, faction       -->
<!-- goodwill, and chance mechanics. 3 turns.                    -->
<!-- Precond: player rank veteran+, not on Cordon                -->
<!-- ========================================================== -->

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_precond">
    <text>req_rank:veteran,req_not_level:l01_escape</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_timeout">
    <text>100</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_timeout_msg">
    <text>Window's closing, $player_name. Don't say I didn't warn you. Out.</text>
</string>

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_open">
    <text>$player_name, got intel you need to hear. One of my contacts saw a bandit squad setting up an ambush near %dark_valley_panda_st%. They're targeting anyone heading through the valley in the next few hours. Looked like 6-8 men, armed heavy. You're a $player_rank, so I'm giving you first crack at this info. What do you want to do with it?</text>
</string>

<!-- Turn 1 Choices -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_choice_1">
    <text>Good intel. I'll set up a counter-ambush. Mark the location.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_choice_2">
    <text>How reliable is your contact? I don't walk into traps on hearsay.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_choice_3">
    <text>Any way to avoid the area entirely? What routes are clear?</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_choice_4">
    <text>Interesting. What if we could redirect them into mutant territory?</text>
</string>

<!-- Turn 1 Replies -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_reply_1">
    <text>Marking now. They're dug in near the road, using the factory buildings for cover. If you hit them from the east ridge, you'll have elevation advantage. Be fast though, they'll scatter if they spot you early. I'll spread the word that the ambush got broken. Good for everyone's reputation.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_reply_2">
    <text>My contact's solid. Ex-military, runs a trading route through the valley twice a week. He nearly walked into it himself, spotted the lookout just in time. This isn't secondhand gossip, $player_name. But I understand being careful. What else do you need?</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_reply_3">
    <text>The northern pass through the truck cemetery is clear last I heard, but it adds hours to any route south. The bandits picked their spot well, it's a natural chokepoint. If you're not looking for a fight, go wide and stay off the main roads.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_reply_4">
    <text>Now that's creative. There's a known den not far from their position. If someone made enough noise in the right spot... the mutants might do the dirty work for us. Risky, but if it works, problem solved without wasting ammo. You'd have to get close though.</text>
</string>

<!-- Turn 1 Outcomes -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_outcome_1">
    <text>watch_location_trigger:st_val_smart_terrain_8_6_name:spawn_hostile:bandit:10:100,reward_rep:15,reward_gw:10:stalker</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_outcome_2">
    <text>none</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_outcome_3">
    <text>reward_gw:5:stalker</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_outcome_4">
    <text>none</text>
</string>

<!-- Turn 1 Continuations -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_cont_1">
    <text>0</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_cont_2">
    <text>2</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_cont_3">
    <text>0</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_cont_4">
    <text>2</text>
</string>

<!-- ===== TURN 2: Investigation / Mutant lure follow-up ===== -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_choice_1">
    <text>Alright, I believe you. Mark the ambush site, I'm going in.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_choice_2">
    <text>Show me where the mutant den is. I like the redirect plan.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_choice_3">
    <text>What's in it for you? Why share this for free?</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_choice_4">
    <text>I'll handle it my way. Thanks for the warning.</text>
</string>

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_reply_1">
    <text>Location sent. Good luck, $player_name. Hit them hard and fast. Every stalker who hears those bandits got cleaned out will sleep easier tonight. I'll owe you one after this.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_reply_2">
    <text>Marking the den location now. It's southeast of their position, maybe 200 meters. Something nasty lives in there, I've heard dogs and worse at night. Fire a few shots near the entrance and run back toward the bandit position. Let nature take its course. Just... don't get caught in the middle.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_reply_3">
    <text>Free? Nothing's free. I trade through that valley too. Those bandits shut down the route, I lose income. You clear them out, my supply line opens back up. Mutual benefit, $player_name. That's how the Zone works.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_reply_4">
    <text>Your call, stalker. Just watch yourself out there. Those bandits aren't rookies if they're setting up organized ambushes. Stay sharp.</text>
</string>

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t2_outcome_1">
