<!-- ===== TURN 3: Player questioned the NPC's motives ===== -->
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_choice_1">
    <text>Fair enough. Business is business. Mark the location, I'll handle it.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_choice_2">
    <text>If your trade route matters that much, pay me to clear it. 3000 RU.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_choice_3">
    <text>Mutual benefit sounds right. I'll take the intel and the mutant den location.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_choice_4">
    <text>Nah, I don't do other people's dirty work. Deal with it yourself.</text>
</string>

<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_reply_1">
    <text>Respect, $player_name. Coordinates sent. Wipe them out and the whole valley benefits. I'll make sure people know who cleaned house.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_reply_2">
    <text>3000? Steep, but if you actually clear that chokepoint... fine. Transferring now. Don't spend it all on vodka. Location marked.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_reply_3">
    <text>Smart. Both locations marked. The ambush site and the den. However you play it, those bandits need to go. May the Zone favor the bold, $player_name.</text>
</string>
<string id="st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_3_t3_reply_4">
    <text>Dirty work? I call it survival. But fine, I'll find someone else. Don't come crying when those bandits are taxing every route in the valley. Out.</text>
</string>

